{"author":{"id":"27a92b445112509f896fbafb1295a63babb443b0af855b44b6dc09c14110e240"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1598101207,"nonce":"jR3wuRDCmhai7co5kwG3/jtMtGs=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY3ODYzODIyMQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug/issues/445#issuecomment-678638221"},"message":"This is because git-bug has a cache/index. When you are pushing to `a`, this cache is not updated because git-bug is not running. It's a simple `git push` of all the bug/identities data, stored in git branches.\n\nThis is usually fine as the remote is usually a server where no one will try to read the bugs but it can come as a problem as you have seen. A solution would likely a git hook to update the cache when refs are pushed.\n\nClosing as this is the same thing as https://github.com/MichaelMure/git-bug/issues/409","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1598101207,"nonce":"5ircDllAwVliKWwhzMMtVZYZfXc=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50MzY4MTk5NjA3Nw=="},"status":2}]}